title: Young German violinist to play at WWU Saturday
text: Print this article Advertisement COLLEGE PLACE â€” Fifteen-year-old violinist Ariane Dernbach will play at 7:30 p.m. Saturday at the Melvin K. West Fine Arts Center Auditorium, Walla Walla University campus, 204 S. College Ave. Dernbach, from Darmstadt, Germany, is on a concert tour in the U.S. with a program of works by Rachmaninov, Beethoven, Tchaikovsky, Massenet, Brahms, Saint-Saens and Vitali. The concert is free. For more information, call 509-527-2563. More like this story
